Peru Stocks: Alturas, Candente, Minera IRL, Relapasa, Telefonica

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-06-14T18:47:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/peru-stocks-alturas-candente-minera-irl-relapasa-telefonica.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:23 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose 0.2 percent to 20,639.01. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 0.5 percent to 2,624.25.  Industrial, banking and utility stocks rebounded after U.S.
stocks gained, BBVA Banco Continental chief analyst Miguel Leiva
said in a telephone interview.  Telefonica del Peru SAA (TEF PE), the local unit of
 Telefonica SA (TEF) , rose 3.3 percent to $23.58. Corp. Aceros Arequipa
SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, gained 1.8 percent
to 2.79 soles. Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of
 Spain ’s Repsol YPF SA, climbed 1.7 percent to 1.81 soles after
crude surged in New York.  Banco Continental SA (CONTINC1)  (CONTINC1 PE),
the local unit of Spain’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA,
rose 1.5 percent to 6.60 soles.  Miners gained after metals advanced in New York and  London .  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, rose 6.7 percent to 16 cents.  Minera IRL
Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in
Peru, gained 4.4 percent to $1.20 after announcing it increased
reserves at its Ollachea gold deposit.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT) 
, a Canadian exploration company, rose 3.5 percent to
$1.49.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  